wikipedia_page.main: Godfrey Fetherstonhaugh  ( FAN-shaw; 11 April 1858 – September 1928) was an Irish Unionist Party politician. He was elected at the 1906 general election as Member of Parliament (MP) for North Fermanagh, and held the seat until he resigned from the House of Commons on 16 October 1916 by taking the post of Steward of the Manor of Northstead.

link_mentions.page: List of MPs elected in the January 1910 United Kingdom general election

response: The North Fermanagh by-election of 1916 was held on 27 October 1916.  The by-election was held due to the resignation of the incumbent Irish Unionist MP, Godfrey Fetherstonhaugh.  It was won by the Irish Unionist candidate Edward Archdale who was unopposed due to a War-time electoral pact.
